         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper a new variational method is proposed for the numerical approximation of the solution of the forward-backward heat equation. The approach consists of first reducing the second-order problem to an equivalent first-order system, and then using a finite element procedure with continuous elements in both space and time for the numerical approximation. Under suitable regularity assumptions, error estimates and the results of some numerical experiments are presented.</p>
          </abstract>
